mappingRules.description: The cell value must not be in the list of specified items (Comma separated)

mappingRules.functionBody: (function(s, arr, p, rowData, pm) { let fnText = arr[0]; const fn = new Function('s','arr','rowData', 'pm', fnText); return { status: 'success', data: fn(s, arr, rowData, pm) }; })

functionData.title: JavaScript expression:
functionData.value: const urlObj = new URL(rowData.secondaryViewHref); const hashString = urlObj.hash.substring(1);   const params = new URLSearchParams(hashString);  const variantId = params.get("variant_id"); if (variantId !== null) {   params.set("id", variantId); }  if (params.get("model") === "product.template") {   params.set("model", "product.product"); }  urlObj.hash = params.toString();  return urlObj.toString().trim();

mappingRules.description: Manipulates (and returns the result of) the cell value given the javascript expression. Available parameters are: s (original value), rowData (the existing row containing rowData.cells which is the accessors, and other settings. See console)

functionData.value: const urlObj = new URL(rowData.secondaryViewHref);   const hashString = urlObj.hash.substring(1);   const params = new URLSearchParams(hashString);    const variantId = params.get("variant_id");   if (variantId !== null) {     return variantId;   }  return "";

mappingRules.description: Manipulates (and returns the result of) the cell value given the javascript expression. Available parameters are: s (original value), rowData (the existing row containing rowData.cells which is the accessors, and other settings. See console)

mappingRules.functionBody: (function(s, arr, p, rowData, pm) { s = Number(s.toString().trim()); const numberOfDecimalsToRoundTo = arr[0]; s = s.toFixed(numberOfDecimalsToRoundTo).toString(); s = s.replace('.', arr[1]); s = s.replace(',', arr[1]); return { status: 'success', data: s }; })
mappingRules.description: Converts the cell value to a number and adds the specified number of decimals. This does round the number. It also changes the decimal indicator to the specified character
